Our strucrure imposes to place in strictly distinct paragraphs : 
1. what is general and simple and should be printed in all reports. It should not include observatory-specific figure as it will be printed in both observatory-specific report, and an observatory-specific report should not include mention to figures from the other observatory
2. what is relative to Marovoay and will be printed into consolidated report and printed Marovoay-specific report
3. what is specific to Alaotra and will be printed into consolidated report and printed Alaotra-specific report
4. what is technical, either specific on one observatory, or common, and printed into both.
In the text we have several paragraphs that are simple and include figures from both observatories. This is not appropriate.
In all cases, we should avoid to have in the prose sections (text outside code chunks) any figure aggregating data from both observatories, for instance in Foncier.
In the consolidated report, comments of a graph should include paragraphs specific to marovoay, comments specifics to alaotra. They can be preceded or followed by comments on both, but if simple they should not include figures from one or another observatory. And if complex they can include figures from both, but it should be reserved for technical aspcets that are too technical for the general public (local stakeholders).